# Invobolt — environment variables
#
# Instant mode (v0.1, this repo) needs NO environment variables at all:
# the generator runs entirely in the browser.
#
# The variables below configure the OPTIONAL workspace mode (v0.2). They are
# read only when WORKSPACE_ENABLED=true; leave it unset and the build ignores
# them entirely.

# --- Workspace mode (v0.2, opt-in) ---
# Off by default: leave WORKSPACE_ENABLED unset and the app is exactly the
# instant-mode-only build (no accounts, no database, no env vars needed).
# Set it to "true" AND provide DATABASE_URL to mount the /app workspace.
# Must be exactly "true" — any other value reads as off.
# WORKSPACE_ENABLED=true

# Postgres connection string (Neon is the documented default; any Postgres works).
# Apply the app schema (clients, invoices) with `pnpm run db:migrate`.
#
# On Vercel this is automatic: the `vercel-build` script migrates before the
# build, so a deployment's tables exist before it serves traffic. That step is
# gated on WORKSPACE_ENABLED — with the flag off it skips, keeping the
# instant-mode build free of any database. With the flag on and this unset, the
# build fails on purpose rather than shipping an /app that throws on first use.
# DATABASE_URL=

# Authentication is handled by Neon Auth (Managed Better Auth). Enable Neon Auth
# on your Neon project, then set the values it gives you. Neon Auth manages its
# own user tables in the `neon_auth` schema and sends magic-link emails itself —
# no separate email provider is needed for sign-in.
#
# Base URL of your Neon Auth instance.
# NEON_AUTH_BASE_URL=https://your-project.neon.tech
# Secret for signing session cookies — must be at least 32 chars.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
# NEON_AUTH_COOKIE_SECRET=

# --- Email delivery (v0.3, optional) ---
# Sends invoices from the editor (and recurring auto-send) via Resend. Both
# values are required together; with either unset the Send UI simply doesn't
# render. The email links to the shared invoice page — no attachment.
#
# The From address. Must be on a domain verified in Resend.
# EMAIL_FROM=invoices@yourdomain.com
# RESEND_API_KEY=
#
# Per-user sends per rolling 24h (anti-abuse). Default: 20.
# EMAIL_DAILY_CAP=20

# --- Recurring invoices (v0.3, optional) ---
# Shared secret for /api/cron/recurring — the route 404s until this is set.
# On Vercel, setting CRON_SECRET makes the platform send it automatically with
# the cron defined in vercel.json (daily). Self-hosters: point any scheduler
# at GET /api/cron/recurring with "Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>".
# Generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
# CRON_SECRET=

# --- Stripe import (v0.3, always optional) ---
# The import UI asks the user to PASTE a read-only restricted key (rk_...),
# which is used for that import only and never stored — on a hosted
# multi-tenant deployment there is nothing to configure here.
#
# Self-hosting your own single-user instance? Optionally set the key below and
# the import runs with it when the paste field is left empty. Restricted keys
# only (Developers -> API keys -> Create restricted key, with read access to
# Customers and Products); a secret key (sk_...) is refused by shape.
# STRIPE_RESTRICTED_KEY=
